#12208
The Eastern Plains~
You find yourself just off from the town's large stone wall.  At your feet
the color of the grass turns to a sicker brown instead of the fresher green you
would expect within the safety of a town.  But as the grass wears thin, it
picks up into a wide dirt area, almost a trail.  Though this hasn't been worn
by the footsteps of travellers, it is the vast years of harsh weather the
outter lands are subjected to through the seasons.
